Compilation flags:
========================================
Enable : MODEL=HYDRO, PARTICLE, GRAVITY, DUAL_ENERGY, STAR_FORMATION, FEEDBACK
Disable: COMOVING


Simulation setup:
========================================
1. Units:
   (1) External (for Input__TestProb only):
       See the comment of each runtime variable

   (2) Internal (for all other input files and internal usage):
       [L] = 1.0    kpc
       [M] = 1.0e10 Msun
       [V] = 1.0    km/s
    -->[T] = 978.5  Myr
    -->[D] = [M]/[D]^3 = 10 Msun/pc^3 ~ 6.768e-22 g/cm^3

2. Default setup resolution
   (1) Highest resolution ~ 3.4 pc (root grid 256^3; MAX_LEVEL = 9)
       --> cell mass = 10.0 Msun


Note:
========================================
1. Simulate the isolated WLM dwarf galaxy
2. Some handy yt analysis scripts are put at "yt_script"
3. To run higher-resolution for the outflow regions, turn on `OPT__FLAG_USER` and
   edit the "Cell_Position" column in `Input__Flag_User`,
   which specify the bottom-left coordinates of a central cube to refine into a higher level
4. To run simulations with resolution double everywhere and add an extra level for low-dt regions
   - `Input__Parameter`
     REGRID_COUNT                  1
     FLAG_BUFFER_SIZE_MAXM1_LV     1
     FLAG_BUFFER_SIZE_MAXM2_LV     4
     MAX_LEVEL                     11
     OPT__FLAG_USER                1
     SF_CREATE_STAR_MIN_LEVEL      10
     SF_CREATE_STAR_MAX_GAS_JEANSL 2.0
     FB_LEVEL                      10
   - `Input__Flag_Rho`
     ```
     # Level                         Density
           0                  2.30140136e-11
           1                  1.84112109e-10
           2                  1.47289687e-09
           3                  1.17831750e-08
           4                  9.42654001e-08
           5                  7.54123201e-07
           6                  6.03298561e-06
           7                  4.82638848e-05
           8                  3.86111079e-04
           9                  3.08888863e-03
          10                  2.47111090e+22
     ```
